# vvaharness — long-context Ollama variant.
#
# WHY: Ollama defaults num_ctx to ~2k–4k and SILENTLY TRUNCATES any prompt that
# exceeds it. vvaharness packs large multi-file prompts, so a default-context
# model returns garbage/empty. This Modelfile bakes in a 32k window that matches
# the budgets in ./config.yaml (chunk_token_budget 20000 + 6000 output ≈ 26k).
#
# BUILD:
#   ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:14b
#   ollama create qwen2.5-coder-14b-32k -f ./Modelfile
# Then in .env:  OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5-coder-14b-32k
# (This model already exists in your Ollama — it was renamed from the earlier
#  misleading "qwen3.6-32k". Rebuild only if you delete it.)
#
# Swap FROM to match whatever base you pulled (must support tools + JSON).
# Raise num_ctx if your VRAM allows AND you raise chunk_token_budget in
# config.yaml to match — keep (chunk_token_budget + max output) < num_ctx.

FROM qwen2.5-coder:14b

# 32k context window. This is the knob that actually prevents truncation; the
# OpenAI-compat /v1 endpoint cannot set it per-request, so it must live here.
PARAMETER num_ctx 32768

# Deterministic-ish analysis. The openai backend may also send temperature and
# auto-drop it on rejection; this is the model-side default.
PARAMETER temperature 0.2
